title: The Souffle Rises
description: When Mike gets concerned about appearing light-weight, he makes an ill-advised editorial about Macedonia. Martin interviews a difficult child prodigy, while Brooke interviews Ugly Dave Gray.

title: The Desert Angel
description: Problems emerge when Frontline show a moving memorial to a missing aid worker, and later find out that she has turned up alive. Brooke interviews a "close friend", tennis player Pat Cash.

title: City of Fear
description: The team do a story on a local serial killer. Mike has problems with his fan mail.

title: She's Got the Look
description: When Brian hires an attractive female sports star as a Frontline presenter, several members of the team are put out.

title: The Siege
description: Mike does a live interview with a gunman who is holding his children hostage during a siege.

title: Playing the Ego Card
description: Mike travels to Bougainville to make an in-depth report about their civil war, leaving Brooke to fill in as host for the week.

title: We Ain't Got Dames
description: When the latest ratings show a decline in the number of female viewers, Frontline makes some changes to halt the slump. Mike appears on World Series Debating.

title: The Art of Gentle Persuasion
description: When Martin tries to interview the husband of the victim of a crocodile attack, he has to resort to some unusual methods to get it. Mike does an expose on table-top dancing.

title: The Invisible Man
description: Brooke uses hidden cameras to do a series of stories. When Mike gets concerned about his low profile, he appears on a telethon.

title: Add Sex and Stir
description: Martin becomes unhappy when he is forced to take a holiday. Brooke does a story on a female cricketer who has been sacked from the national team because she's not a lesbian.

title: Smaller Fish to Fry
description: As they prepare to re-negotiate their contracts for another year, the Frontline team do a series of stories on shonky repairmen, which encourages Mike to try going after one of the "big fish" of the industry.

title: Judge and Jury
description: Brooke does a series of stories about a priest who has been accused of rape. Mike takes a stand against the network using Frontline to cross-promote their other shows. Martin makes an entire butterfly species extinct.

title: This Night of Nights
description: Mike has trouble finding someone to take with him on a date to the Logie Awards.

title: One Big Family
description: A new person takes over as executive producer of Frontline. The network plan its promotions.

title: Workin' Class Man
description: Martin is given a hard story about an ostrich farm. The team try to make the show more appealing to a working-class audience.

title: Heroes and Villains
description: The Frontline team start a debate on racism. Brooke finds it hard to portray a heart surgeon as a hero.

title: Office Mole
description: When Mike becomes bored, he is appointed as an international story coordinator. All of Frontline's stories appear to be being stolen by A Current Affair.

title: Basic Instincts
description: A brutal bashing is recorded by a Frontline camera operator. Emma has a new boyfriend. Mike sets up a debate on euthanasia that turns out to be less than successful.

title: Let the Children Play
description: Mike receives a visit from his niece. Frontline "borrow" A Current Affair's idea of a playground construction challenge story.

title: Keeping Up Appearances
description: A gay magazine has Mike in its cover photo. Brooke interviews an acid attack victim.

title: Divide the Community, Multiply the Ratings
description: Frontline raise the issue of ethnic tensions within a community.

title: All Work and No Fame
description: When Mike becomes bored again, he itches to get his hands dirty on a story.

title: Changing the Face of Current Affairs
description: Network management hire an American consultant in order to rejuvenate Frontline's image.

title: A Man of His Convictions
description: When Mike again gets concerned about appearing light-weight, he joins a protest by The Wilderness Society, and gets himself arrested.

title: The Great Pretenders
description: Frontline appoint a new legal advisor. Martin bails out a Nazi. Mike plays for an unusual home viewer on Jackpot.

title: Give 'em Enough Rope
description: The Frontline team attend the premiere of their network's new soap opera, Rainbow Island. An artist provides Brooke with an interesting self-portrait. Mike interviews the owner of the network.

title: Dick on the Line
description: Frontline has another new executive producer. Mike considers going to the ABC.

title: My Generation
description: Mike gets concerned that Frontline is ignoring its younger audience.

title: The Shadow We Cast
description: Frontline try to expose Pauline Hanson as a xenophobe. Geoff attempts to explain a metaphor to Mike.

title: One Rule for One
description: When Mike receives some death threats, he hires a bodyguard. Martin gets suspended for four months.

title: A Hole in the Heart: Part 1
description: Frontline try to save the life of a boy who has a hole in his heart. Brooke makes an announcement to the team.

title: A Hole in the Heart: Part 2
description: Following her announcement, Brooke has an important decision to make. Mike tries to play a round of golf with Ian Baker-Finch.

title: The Simple Life
description: Frontline does a profile on the unemployed Baxter family. Mike is revealed as Australia's fourth richest entertainer.

title: I Get the Big Names
description: Mike tries to secure an interview with Mel Gibson.

title: The Art of the Interview
description: Sunday Forum's new producer is educated by Graeme in the art of the interview.

title: 'I' Disease
description: Frontline gets a new segment producer. Mike writes his life story, and has an accident with a sign language translator.

title: Addicted to Fame
description: Mike makes a decision to abandon publicity. Geoffrey's weather special proves to be a huge success.

title: The Code
description: When This Is Your Life make Mike their star guest, Martin becomes the episode's researcher. Mike sacks Elliot, the regular Friday night funny-man.

title: Epitaph
description: Mike flies to a remote Aboriginal community when he goes on a health crusade.
